      <p>This is a plain-English summary. The binding DPA text is provided as a separate document or annex.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Roles:</strong> Client = Controller; Endora (Marco Luyckx) = Processor.</li>
        <li><strong>Subject:</strong> Guest concierge processing for the contract term.</li>
        <li><strong>Nature/Purpose:</strong> handle guest inquiries; route recommendations; optional follow-ups.</li>
        <li><strong>Data:</strong> chat content, timestamps, session IDs, truncated IP/device, optional contact.</li>
        <li><strong>TOMs:</strong> encryption in transit, access controls, logging, minimization, deletion.</li>
        <li><strong>Sub-processors:</strong> Azure OpenAI (EU), Hetzner (DE), IONOS (DE); optional Google Ireland (EU) if enabled.</li>
        <li><strong>Transfers:</strong> EU-hosted; third-country only if mandated by Client with SCCs.</li>
        <li><strong>Assistance:</strong> DSARs, security, DPIAs (reasonable efforts).</li>
        <li><strong>Breach:</strong> notify without undue delay if Client data is affected.</li>
        <li><strong>End-of-term:</strong> delete/return data per Client instruction & legal duties.</li>
        <li><strong>Audits:</strong> reasonable documentation/co-operation; on-site by arrangement & at Client cost.</li>
